flowRoot.flowPara: The read-only scheduler is a static html/css matrix. An event reserves Spaces and schedules a TimeSpan. An event can reserve multiple Spaces but only occurs over a single TimeSpan. A typical Event will reserve a single Space.
The JS enabled version allows drag and drop to alter event reservation times and the event's reserved space.
The changes display immediately and are tagged with a 'changed' class for distinction.
Masquerade Rehearsal Part 1 is rescheduled for 3PM to 4:30PM in Main Events C.
The changes can be pushed to the database triggering update notifications.
A change list is built up in plain language.
Currently the Spaces controller will respond to show requests for format.ics with an icalendar formatted list of all events scheduled in the space.
There is no means to put data yet, but that could also be done. Otherwise a more generic json API could be provided.
